A highlight was an amazing English Afternoon tea which was better than any I've had at the Ritz in London.	The hotel itself is small but inviting and has a very proper english vibe.	The hotel bar is upscale but comfortable and inviting.	The hotel was very apologetic about the situation, but it had little bearing on anything other than trying to get a cab.	OK we didn't like Vancouver, but loved this Hotel, which was the saving grace really.	They have computers in the business center which are free - with small screens and slow access but better than nothing!	The rooms are small but very nice and the bathrooms seem newly updated.